{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN REVIEW · PASS 1 · [G6] Approach soundness, anti-patterns & alternative-selection — VERDICT: CLEAN (no findings).\n\nGrounded the review in the live eval seam. (1) MECHANISM CORRECTNESS: the plan's premises check out against the code — `run_eval()` is a genuine NotImplementedError stub (src/rebar/llm/eval.py:319,346), `validate_scorer` exists and enforces the cross-family/temperature-0/seed/snapshot grader discipline the plan extends (eval.py:107-160), and `verify_completion`/`review_ticket`/`scan_spec` are genuinely agentic (verify_completion runs through gate_dispatch reading store+repo via tools, completion.py:169-225), which justifies the \"context-injection solver + stubbed/fixture-backed repo tools\" path rather than inline-feeding. The two-tier mechanism (zero-cost deterministic gate on every PR + LLM-judge tier off the critical path) achieves the regression-gating goal without putting paid model calls on the PR blocking path. (2) FITNESS: solves the named problem (a prompt edit is currently a blind cutover) rather than a proxy — Success Criterion explicitly requires an eval that SCORES output, not one that only shape-validates the spec. (3) ALTERNATIVES considered & discarded: (a) gate live LLM-judge evals directly on every PR — rejected as worse on cost/blast-radius/fork-safety, exactly what the plan's two-tier split avoids; (b) inline-feed reviewer inputs instead of a context-injection solver — not viable because the reviewers read store+repo via tools, so the chosen solver+stub approach is codebase-aligned. The chosen approach is defensibly at-least-as-good on all axes; alternatives discarded, not written into the plan. (4) POSITIVE RATIONALE present: the story states why (\"regression-gated, not a blind cutover\"; deterministic-cheap-PR vs expensive-judge-off-path aligned to community consensus; fork-safety/spend-cap rails).\n\nAffirmations (G6): mechanism correctness (grounded against eval.py + completion.py); 